
[1]apposition

   APPOSI'TION, n.

   1. The act of adding to; addition; a setting to.

   By the opposition of new matter.

   2. In Grammar, the placing of two nouns, in the same case, without a
   connecting word between them, as, I admire Cicero, the orator. In this
   case, the second noun explains or characterizes the first.
